ygData.messageBody:
The past two replies were both right. On the server I started on, I
had NEVER heard that phrase before. On the server I play on now, it's
quite common to hear that. If you ever used to frequent chat rooms,
remember how people used to say "asl check"? It's the same stupid
thing. I hate when people do that. All it means is people have an
open spot in their group, so they're looking for a suitable person to
occupy the spot. Maybe I'm old-fashioned, but I still stick with "Is
there anyone lfg?"...

Laielenie
lvl 32 cleric
Fennin Ro server
